Start Making £30 An Hour Just for Playing ‘Fortnite’

With over 3 million people playing the game ‘Fortnite: Battle Royale’, it has officially become a widespread addiction for people of all ages. But just how out of control is this gaming epidemic? 

A number of parents have spoken up in protest of the game, claiming that it has negatively impacted their children in a big way. One mother says that she barely even recognizes her own son because of how obsessed he has become with Fortnite.

Those who literally have the skills to pay the bills can make £30 an hour playing this online multiplayer game. There are also moneymaking opportunities for, particularly talented FIFA and Call of Duty players.

Divine is a website where pro gamer wannabes can go to help beginners hone their skills in exchange for some decent pay.
As long as you have come in first a minimum of 25 times, you can become a professional Fortnite tutor. The better you are at the game, the more money you are likely to make. 

There is a TON of demand for skilled gamers who can transform noobs into pros. When someone is looking for a Fortnite coach, they post their details, including which specific area they need help with. Coaches place bids for their services and start helping beginners not to suck anymore.

There is no question that it takes talent to be truly good at playing Fortnite, but there are already thousands of people signing up to be coaches and get tutored.

Tyler Blevins is a prime example of how potentially lucrative this arrangement can be for some people. The 26-year-old has made around $560,000 a month streaming himself playing Fortnite. A number of his videos have gone viral, amassing millions of views within a single day.

Blevins currently has over 500,000 followers on Twitch and over 350,000 on YouTube. He has said that streaming his gameplay on these websites has changed his life in a big way. He went from living with his parents to owning a house in an upscale neighborhood and driving a BMW.

If your channel really blows up like Blevins’, you become eligible for Twitch partner status. This will allow you to start taking paid subscriptions and even sell merchandise. You will also get a share of the ad revenue.

Becoming a tutor for others isn’t the only way to make money playing Fortnite. You can also sign up for tournaments that will put your skills to the test. Each participant must pay a small entry fee of just a few dollars.

Those who win these tournaments can collect their prize via PayPal. With prizes ranging from $100 to $200 per tournament, skilled players can easily make a ton of cash. The leagues and ladders are longer tournaments that can take weeks to finish, but the prizes are bigger.

Cody Foltz is another young person who has made a small fortune from video game streaming. He claims to have once made $10,000 in just one week of playing Fortnite.

The Esports Hub is a platform that hosts as many as 20 tournaments per day. Jonathon Kinloch is the managing director of the platform, and even he is amazed at how massive the community has gotten.

This is how the free video game 'Fortnite' might make more than $3 billion annually. It all comes down to a frenzied player base that is eager to spend real money on virtual currencies that don't have any impact on actual gameplay.

Chances are you've heard of a video game called "Fortnite."

It's a massively popular game that is generating hundreds of millions of dollars each month in revenue. But unlike other popular online games like Activision Blizzard's "Call of Duty" franchise, "Fortnite" is free to play.

How is it that a free game is on pace to make $3.5 billion this year alone?

It all comes down to the in-game purchases made by gamers from around the world. Players exchange real cash for virtual cash known as V-Bucks. This allows players to buy upgraded skins for their characters and even unlock certain rewards. Even though these upgrades don't give players a competitive edge, that hasn't stopped gamers spending hundreds of millions of dollars a month on them.

SuperData, a research firm that specializes in video games, estimated that Epic Games' "Fortnite" generated nearly $296 million in April. Multiply that number by 12 and "Fortnite" has the possibility of generating $3.5 billion in revenue annually. Epic Games recently announced that it is jumping into the esports scene. The gaming studio said that it will be funding $100 million in esports prize pools for "Fortnite."

I finally got it to work... recent versions of Auto hotkey (I already had it for Path of exile) do not have a template so here is what you need to do
-Go into your AHK file in your program files
-copy ANY AHK file and paste it into the same folder
-right click the "copied" file and go into properties
-click security
-click edit
-highlight users, hit add and check "full control"
-in a txt box, type "Everyone" (i would make sure to capitalize the E just incase)
-hit ok/apply
-go back into AHK folder
-right click the copied file (can be renamed already) 
-Paste the code over the copied txt
-save 
-(I double clicked it after saving and I am not sure if that activated it or not)
-Gratz!!! now you can cheat on roblox, cookie clicker, or whatever idle clicker esk game you desire
